What few have talked about is how demystifying IG stories have been for the decadence of the bourgeoisie. Young college guys look at videos of Dan Bilzerian and other "hypermasculine" figures and can not help but worryingly notice how similar their idols' parties are to their own

Yes, there are 200 supermodels, but those guys will sleep with no more than like 2 or 3 of them, right? And, yes, the breasts are larger, and the alcohol is more expensive, and so is the coke. But the difference is not that big, is it?

Is this all there is to life, to hedonism?

The young fella begins to wonder: this can not be the greatest possible pleasure and happiness in the world - it is scarcely different from his own life! So, he suspects, there must be something else, something greater than this. A seeker of The Path is born from this knowledge.
People are so numb to romance they see it as pornographic, what a tragedy!
